ap|25 kV 50 Hz}} in countries where {{nowrap|60 Hz}} is the normal grid power frequency.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:20%\" | Country\n! style=\"width:20%\" | Location\n! style=\"width:25%\" | Name of system\n! style=\"width:35%\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Montreal]]\n| [[Deux-Montagnes Line (AMT)|Deux-Montagnes Line]]\n| built by [[Canadian Northern Railway|CNoR]] in 1918 as 3000 V DC, converted to 25&nbsp;[[Volt|kV]]&nbsp;[[Alternating current|AC]]/60&nbsp;[[Hertz|Hz]] in 1995 by [[Autorit\u00e9 r\u00e9gionale de transport m\u00e9tropolitain|ARTM]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Japan}} Japan\n| [[Kant\u014d region|Kant\u014d]] (west of Tokyo), [[Ch\u016bbu region|Ch\u016bbu]], [[Kansai region|Kansai]], [[Ch\u016bgoku region|Ch\u016bgoku]], and [[Kyushu]] regions\n| [[Tokaido Shinkansen|T\u014dkaid\u014d]]-[[Sany\u014d Shinkansen|Sany\u014d]] [[Shinkansen]]<br>[[Hokuriku Shinkansen]] (sections between [[Karuizawa Station|Karuizawa]] - [[J\u014detsumy\u014dk\u014d Station|J\u014detsumy\u014dk\u014d]], and between [[Itoigawa Station|Itoigawa]] - [[Kanazawa Station|Kanazawa]])<br>[[Kyushu Shinkansen]]\n| [[25 kV AC#50 Hz|50&nbsp;Hz]] in eastern Japan; see [[List of railway electrification systems#25 kV AC 50&nbsp;Hz overhead|25 kV AC 50&nbsp;Hz overhead]] above\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{flagicon|South Korea}} [[South Korea]]\n| South Korea\n| [[Korail]]\n| all Korail freight/passenger lines except [[Seoul subway]] Line 3 (see [[List of railway electrification systems#1500 V DC overhead|1500&nbsp;V&nbsp;DC overhead]] above)\n|-\n|[[Seoul]]\n|[[Shinbundang Line|Shinbundang line]]\n|\n|-\n| [[Incheon]], [[Seoul]]\n| [[A'REX]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Mexico}} Mexico\n| [[Mexico City]]\n| [[Ferrocarril Suburbano de la Zona Metropolitana del Valle de M\u00e9xico]]\n| &nbsp;<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.fsuburbanos.com/secciones/espacio_viajero/conoce_trenes.php?ver=prestaciones| title=Espacio del Viajero: Conoce los Trenes| 