 plans DC/AC switch in May - Times of India|author=|date=|website=timesofindia.com|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref>) respectively\n|-\n|[[Mumbai]]\n| [[Line 1 (Mumbai Metro)|Mumbai Metro (Line 1)]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Chennai|Chennai (Madras)]]\n| [[Chennai Metro]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| [[Delhi]]\n| [[Delhi Metro]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Iran]]\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| Planned\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Israel}} Israel\n| &nbsp;\n| [[Israel Railways]]\n| Construction contract awarded in December 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Israel Railways awards USD 500m electrification contract to Spanish SEMI|url=http://www.think-railways.com/israel-railways-awards-usd-500m-electrification-contract-spanish-semi|accessdate=17 January 2016|publisher=Think Railways}}</ref> Initial test runs began December 2017.\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Italy}} Italy\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| new high-speed lines only\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Japan}} Japan\n| [[Kant\u014d region|Kant\u014d]] (northeast of Tokyo), [[T\u014dhoku region|T\u014dhoku]], and [[Hokkaido]] regions\n| [[East Japan Railway Company|JR East]] [[Tohoku Shinkansen]], [[Joetsu Shinkansen]], and [[Hokuriku Shinkansen]] (sections between [[Tokyo Station|Tokyo]] - [[Karuizawa Station|Karuizawa]], and between [[J\u014detsumy\u014dk\u014d Station|J\u014detsumy\u014dk\u014d]] - [[Itoigawa Station|Itoigawa]])<br>[[Hokkaido Railway Company|JR Hokkaido]] [[Hokkaido Shinkansen]]\n| [[25 kV AC#60 Hz|60&nbsp;Hz]] in some areas, see [[List of railway electrification systems#25 kV AC 60&nbsp;Hz overhead|60&nbsp;Hz overhead]] below.\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Kazakhstan]]\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Latvia}} [[Latvia]]\n| &nbsp;\n| [[Latvian Railways|Latvian Railways (LDz)]]\n| ''Eastern lines only (planned)''\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Lithuania]]\n| Kena \u2014 Kaunas and Lentvaris \u2014 Trakai\n| [[Lithuanian Railways]] (LG)\n| Electrification of Naujoji Vilnia \u2013 Kena \u2014\nGudogai (BCh) route for Vilnius \u2013 Minsk (Belarus) ser