mway]]\n| Half scale trams. Operated 1969-now. Substations have battery banks for back up.\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| 250\n| {{flagicon|USA}} United States\n| Chicago\n| [[Chicago Tunnel Company]]\n| operated 1906\u20131959\n|-\n| 525\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} Switzerland\n| Lauterbrunnen\n| [[Bergbahn Lauterbrunnen-M\u00fcrren]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| 550\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China]]\n| [[Hong Kong]]\n| [[Hong Kong Tramways]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 550\n| {{flagicon|Isle of Man}} [[Isle of Man]]\n| [[Isle of Man]]\n| [[Manx Electric Railway]]\n| including [[Snaefell Mountain Railway]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon|India}} India\n| [[Kolkata]]\n| [[Trams in Kolkata]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 650\n| rowspan=3 | {{flagicon|USA}} United States\n| [[Buffalo, New York]]\n| [[Buffalo Metro Rail]]\n|\n|-\n| [[El Paso, Texas]]\n| [[El Paso Streetcar]]\n|\n|-\n| [[Pittsburgh]]\n| [[Pittsburgh Light Rail]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} Switzerland\n| [[Basel]]\n| [[Trams in Basel|Basel Trams (BVB/BLT)]]\n|\n|-\n| 700\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} Switzerland\n| [[Bex]] \u2013 [[Col de Bretaye]], [[Vaud]]\n| [[Chemin de fer Bex-Villars-Bretaye]]\n|\n|-\n| 740\n| {{flagicon|USA}} USA\n| [[Oklahoma City]]\n| [[Oklahoma City Streetcar]]\n|\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| 800\n| {{flagicon|Poland}} [[Poland]]\n| [[Tricity, Poland|Tricity]]\n| [[Szybka Kolej Miejska (Tricity)]]\n| Operated 1951-1976. Converted to 3,000 V DC in 1976.\n|-\n| 825\n| {{flagicon|USA}} USA\n| [[Portland, Oregon]]\n| [[MAX Light Rail|MAX]], [[TriMet]]\n| light rail sections west of NE 9th Avenue & Holladay Street utilize a 750 V system\n|-\n| 850\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} Switzerland\n| [[Capolago]] \u2013 [[Monte Generoso]], [[Ticino]]\n| [[Ferrovia Monte Generoso|Ferrovia Monte Generoso (MG)]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 900\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} Switzerland\n| Fribourg\n| [[Chemins de fer Fribourgeois Gruy\u00e8re-Fribourg-Morat|Gruyere \u2013 Fribourg \u2013 Morat]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{flagic