rtment/23/events/|title=Ministry of Health of the Russian Federation - The Russian Government|website=government.ru|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref> ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438}}, in short {{lang-ru|\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438|translit=Minzdrav Rossii}}) is an agency of the government of [[Russia]], headquartered in [[Moscow]].<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20080520130333/http://www.minzdravsoc.ru/ministry/contacts/address \u0421\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0444\u043e\u043d\u044b, \u0430\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0441 \u0438 \u0441\u0445\u0435\u043c\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430].\" Ministry of Healthcare and Social Development. Retrieved on 4 December 2010. \"127994, \u0413\u0421\u041f-4, \u0433. \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430, \u0420\u0430\u0445\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0435\u0440, \u0434. 3\"</ref> It is the successor of the former ''Ministry of Health and Social Development'', which was split in two in 2012 under Prime Minister [[Dmitry Medvedev's First Cabinet|Dmitry Medvedev]], with the social security departments being relegated to the newly formed [[Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs (Russia)|Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs]]. [[Veronika Skvortsova]] was the first minister.\n\n==Duties==\nIts main official responsibilities include:\n*developing and implementing state policy in healthcare;\n*developing and implementing federal health programs, including initiatives on\ndiabetes, tuberculosis, health promotion, health education, disease prevention etc.;\n*developing draft legislation and presenting it to the [[State Duma]];\n*governance of federal medical facilities;\n*medical education and manpower development;\n*epidemiological and environmental health monitoring and health statistics;\n*control of infectious diseases;\n* development of health regulations;\n* development of federal standards and recommendations for quality assurance;\n* development and implementation of federal health programs \n*control and licensing of drugs.\n\n== Ministers ==\n* [[Veronika Skvortsova]] (21 May 2012 \u2014 21 January 2020)\n* [[Mikhail Murashko]] (21 January 2020 \u2014 present)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Russia}}\n* {{official website}} {{in lang|ru}}\n\n{{Executive Authorities of Russia}}\n{{Russia topics}}\n\n[[Category:Federal Ministries of Russia|Health]]\n[[Category:Health ministries|Russia]]\n\n\n{{Russia-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name            = Ministry of Health\n| nativename_a    = {{lang|ru|\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438}}\n| seal            = Emblem of Ministry of Health of Russia.svg\n| seal_caption    = \n| picture         = 4713 Ministry of Health, Russia \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438.jpg\n| picture_caption = Ministry headquarters at Rakhmanovsky pereulok, 3, Moscow\n| formed          = {{start date and age|2012}}\n| preceding1      = Ministry of Health and Social Development\n| minister1_name  = [[Mikhail Murashko]]\n| minister1_pfo   = \n| dissolved       = \n| superseding     = \n| jurisdiction    = [[Government of Russia]]\n| headquarters    = Rakhmanovsky pereulok 3, [[Moscow]]\n| coordinates     = {{coord|55|45|54.94|N|37|37|6.97|E|type:landmark_region:RU|display=inline,title}}\n| budget          = 375.6 billion [[